m><span class=title> PoH recap</span><hr size=1> We started off with a few set backs.  The run to the camp site can be done without invisibility, that's how relatively safe is the travel path is.  However we was crippled by the fact we had a couple creatures stuck out of place on the wall (East) so we had a pile of corpses.  And corpse recovery was slow, Inny kept zapping our people pulling corpses.  Also it was our Rogues first time, and Rogues are the best of CR on Hate.  However, once he learned the area, Balrin did an excellent job of pulling corpses.<br>
<br>
After getting the corpses, we began the raid, in which I made one of the biggest screw ups ever (doh) in which I argoed Maestro onto the party.  Good job to the clerics who scrambled and camped in time.  At this point a few people left, with comments they have never been on a PoH raid where Maestro was argoed in the first 15 minutes.  Heh, I don't blame them.  After we raised everyone again, we began.<br>
<br>
There after the raid went relatively smooth, pulls came in a relatively timely manner, and most people stated they was having fun.  Had a couple more deaths here and there, with the exception of our enchanter having more deaths then he should of had it was really good considering we only had like 8 people experienced in PoH.<br>
<br>
We cleared out all the houses except like two in the NE area (which had Revenants) and there was three chests I couldn't pull.  The wander path was spawning faster then we could kill.  Chests run too slow so everytime I ended pulling wanderers and aborting the chests.<br>
<br>
We also didn't pull the upstairs (I don't know how to pull the upstairs yet with Inny up).<br>
<br>
Also, one other problem not everyone brought their 50pp.  Some people at the event contributed more.  Still left Larr shy of his costs, so we compensated him with the first diamond to cover the cost.  I would like to thank those that contributed extra.<br>
<br>
So overall, (also based on the feedback of several people) the raid was a great success.  Some of the veterans of the planes said it went smoother (other then the Maestro incident) then alot of plane raids they have been on in PoH.<br>
<br>
However, please post in this thread whether you thought the raid was a success or failure and why it was.<br>
<br>
Treasure gotten tons of gem,<br>
<br>
- Two Bard pieces that had to go poof <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
- Necro wand<br>
- Enchanter wand<br>
- One warrior piece<br>
- Two Rogue pieces<br>
- Pally shield<br>
- Two (Three?) Cleric armor<br>
- Two Shaman armor<br>
- Two ranger whips<br>
<br>
Next time we will get the Revanents <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I would like to thank everyone who attending, Halagar from Allied Giants to help run the event, and Larr for helping run the event and Fuloo who was kind enough to help out with TPs to PoH even though he wasn't attending the event.<br>
<br>
Zellex<br>
